ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: "In the Chun Lab meetings, we usually present our current projects or give practice talks. The group can be critical, but very much with the intent on improving research or presentation. I always enjoy hearing about the other research and find the comments very helpful to my own research and presentation. It's an interesting, fun lab meeting and I'd really recommend it."

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Having all attention of my research and my presentation style during these lab meetings has been extremely valuable in terms of improving my presentations and focusing my thinking. Many of the comments received during this lab meeting have turned into much more in-depth discussions with my lab members and I feel like I really benefit from a research-oriented lab meeting. I look forward to the meetings.
